  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The diagnosis of infective endocarditis is based on the results of blood culture and findings
      on transeosophageal echocardiography. Cardiac computarized tomography is a new modality,
      mainly used for the imaging of coronary arteries. Its use in the diagnosis of infective
      endocarditis is not well known.The purpose of this study is to establish the use of cardiac
      CT in infective endocarditis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
